Text.SourceString: Whoa, look who’s finally here!//The new farmer, right? I’m <NPCName>Frank</>.
Folks at the tavern have been talking about you.//You should stop by sometime.
The Tavern is pretty old. I hope the town doesn’t ever tear it down to build some shiny new one.//That's why we keep trying our best to take a good care of it...repainting the building and all.
It’s where I grew up, you know.

It’s where I grew up, you know.
Oh, gee! Have you been by my house lately?//The lot gets unkempt so fast.
It really is a waste of time to clean up.//Maybe if I turn it into a garden, other people will help keep it up. I’m too busy to do it all alone.

We’re closed tomorrow. Oh, but if you need me, just pop by my house.//I’ll be there all day.
I cook at home.//<portrait=happy>I love it, and frankly, I’m good at it! Ha!
If somebody asked, sure, I’d sing.//I mean, why the heck not!!
Hmm… Maybe I can get <NPCName>Theo</> to sing with me.
When I first took over the Tavern, the town gave me a recipe book.//You couldn’t ask for a more thoughtful community!
Sure, I use recipes, but I mix my own drinks at the bar sometimes.//No complaints so far.
I cook at home.//<portrait=happy>I love it, and frankly, I’m good at it! Ha!
Heh, heh, heh… Classic! That’s a knee-slapper!//<portrait=normal>You know the funniest jokes.
The cost of living is really low in Coral Island.//I don’t think you need to make a lot to live comfortably.
The islanders here want to see you succeed.//That’s what makes this place special.
If you surround yourself with positive people, soon enough, positivity will be second nature.
Do you need help?
Hello, hello, hello!
<NPCName>Leah</>’s trying to make it big on the internet.//Don’t ask me. I don’t know what it means either.//<portrait=normal>Sometimes she asks if she can record me cooking…for “content,” she says.
I don’t mind.//<portrait=surprised>Who knows? I might become famous! Ha ha.
Make sure to rest and drink plenty of water, <PlayerName>$player</>.
With the work you do, every day must be exhausting.
Make sure to rest well and drink plenty of water, <PlayerName>$player</>.
The work you do must be really exhausting.//Want to pick up something for an energy boost? Heh, heh.
<NPCName>Noah</> and I used to run around the island, terrorizing our parents.
Now I have two cats, and they’re doing it to me.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha. Oh, how the tables have turned!
Out of all the siblings, I was the one who had the tendency to go rogue.//<portrait=surprised>Can you tell? Ha ha!
I guess I grew out of it…
Out of all the siblings, I was the one who had the tendency to go rogue.//<portrait=surprised>Can you tell? Ha ha!
I guess I grew out of it…
<NPCName>Noah</> and I used to run around the island, terrorizing our parents together.
Now I have two cats, and they’re doing it to me.//<portrait=happy>Ha ha. Oh, how the tables have turned!
I left the island to go to college some years ago.//It was a fun time.
But as soon as I graduated, I knew I needed to come back.//I felt like I didn’t belong in the big city, you know?//Was never home to me.
I learned to cook from my mother. But I didn’t actually cook cook until I went away to college.//I didn’t have much choice. I missed my mom’s food, and I was just too far from home.
What was I supposed to do? Go home? Ha ha.

<NPCName>Noah</>’s had glasses since grade school.//You know, you seem to be asking a lot of questions about <NPCName>Noah</>.//Interesting!
Can you say frankly when your name is <NPCName>Frank</>?
Chill, <PlayerName>$player</>. It’s Thursday!
Bookkeeping isn’t one of my strengths.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s just so tedious.
I’d much rather do the physical work. Be the face of the business.//Entertain people, you know what I mean?
My brother likes doing that tedious work, anyway.//He goes in the office and just goes to town with the numbers. People, eh?
My brother takes care of most of the back-of-the-house things, running Fishensips.
You know, like purchasing, collecting receipts…//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, and filing our taxes. Blech.
My brother takes care of a lot of the back end of things, running the Tavern.

Book-keeping is not my strength. It is extremely tedious for my taste.
Pufferfish has an international reputation for finding secluded islands to drill.
I just hope they don’t drill here.
The town is holding the Cherry Blossom Festival near the lake soon.//It’s a whole-day get-together barbeque thing.
I’ll be the proud grill master for the day. Heh, heh.
I need to brush my grill today. Tomorrow is the potluck barbecue already.
<NPCName>Noah</> loves roasted mushrooms, but he doesn’t like them raw for some reason.

I bet it’s because he doesn’t want to clean them off.//<portrait=happy>I won’t lie to you, <PlayerName>$player</>, cleaning mushrooms is the worst part about cooking them. But that boy <NPCName>Noah</> is just lazy! Ha ha.
It’s hard to get out-of-season produce around here, and I really want to make some pumpkin pie.
Ah… I’m in a pickle, aren’t I?

You know, for the beach cleanup.

The general store owner, <NPCName>Sam</> – you know him?//He loves blueberry everything.
Every time he comes to Fishensips, he’s always asking for it.//The fruit, tarts, what else? Hmm.
I tend to sell more pasta dishes in Fall. I wonder why?
I’ve been making more pasta this season. We’re trying to keep up with demand.//You know, get those money!
We get our tea leaves from Beluga Bay.//It’s good quality, but it costs a lot to ship.
There aren’t many plants that can survive the Winter snow.//But then again, in this frozen soil, oh gosh!
It’s even hard to walk!

It’s hard to get out-of-season produce around here, and I really need it to make some tarts.
Ah… I’m in a pickle, aren’t I?
Do you feel like it rains more in Summer than other seasons?
Gotta say a drizzle comes as a pleasant surprise in this heat.
Heh, heh… You got me! I’m hiding from the rain in here.

I suppose I can just chill for the day.

Ah, sorry. Forgot I already asked that.//<portrait=normal>Guess I’m a little preoccupied.
Just enjoying the nice weather before getting the Tavern ready to open.
